00:04:53.440 --> 00:04:57.180
So t is just a scalar.

00:04:57.180 --> 00:04:59.270
And t is between 0 and 1.

00:04:59.270 --> 00:05:02.440
They have told us that over
here, t is between 0 and 1.

00:05:02.440 --> 00:05:03.720
So this is positive.

00:05:03.720 --> 00:05:05.880
This right here is
a positive value.

00:05:05.880 --> 00:05:11.370
And then this right here is also
going to be a positive value.

00:05:11.370 --> 00:05:15.605
t is greater than 0,
and it is less than 1.

00:05:15.605 --> 00:05:17.480
So this is also going
to be a positive value.

00:05:17.480 --> 00:05:18.860
And these are just scalars.

00:05:18.860 --> 00:05:21.050
So this is going to
be the same thing.

00:05:21.050 --> 00:05:23.087
These are just
scaling the magnitude.

00:05:23.087 --> 00:05:24.670
So this is going to
be the same thing.

00:05:24.670 --> 00:05:26.380
These are positive values.

00:05:26.380 --> 00:05:30.602
So this is going to be t times
the absolute value-- actually

00:05:30.602 --> 00:05:31.560
let me not skip a step.

00:05:31.560 --> 00:05:33.893
This is going to be the same
thing as the absolute value

00:05:33.893 --> 00:05:38.840
of t times the absolute
value of z2 minus z1--

00:05:38.840 --> 00:05:40.460
because this is
just scaling it--

00:05:40.460 --> 00:05:48.770
plus the absolute
value of 1 minus t,

00:05:48.770 --> 00:05:51.980
times the absolute
value of z1 minus z2.

00:05:51.980 --> 00:05:55.600
Now let me be clear, the
absolute value of z1 minus z2

00:05:55.600 --> 00:06:00.240
is going to be equal to the
absolute value of z2 minus z1.

00:06:00.240 --> 00:06:02.739
These vectors are just pointing
in different directions,

00:06:02.739 --> 00:06:03.780
or these complex numbers.

00:06:03.780 --> 00:06:05.702
One is just the
negative of the other.

00:06:05.702 --> 00:06:07.660
But their absolute values,
or their magnitudes,

00:06:07.660 --> 00:06:09.100
are going to be the same.

00:06:09.100 --> 00:06:13.050
So let me write z2 minus z1, the
absolute value of z2 minus z1,

00:06:13.050 --> 00:06:13.550
there.

00:06:13.550 --> 00:06:14.660
And the reason why
I'm doing it is

00:06:14.660 --> 00:06:15.900
so I get the same thing here.

00:06:15.900 --> 00:06:17.320
And I can factor it out.

00:06:17.320 --> 00:06:19.940
So the absolute
value of z1 minus z1

00:06:19.940 --> 00:06:21.660
is the same thing as
the absolute value

00:06:21.660 --> 00:06:24.760
of z1 minus z2,
because it's just

00:06:24.760 --> 00:06:26.760
going in the other direction.

00:06:26.760 --> 00:06:28.380
Now, what can we do here?

00:06:28.380 --> 00:06:30.460
Well, the absolute
value of t, remember

00:06:30.460 --> 00:06:34.875
t is positive, so this is
just going to be equal to t.

00:06:34.875 --> 00:06:37.000
The absolute value of 1
minus t, once again, that's

00:06:37.000 --> 00:06:39.650
positive, so that's just
going to be 1 minus t.

00:06:39.650 --> 00:06:43.800
So we can factor
this business out.

00:06:43.800 --> 00:06:50.360
So we're going to
get t plus 1 minus t,

00:06:50.360 --> 00:06:54.970
times the absolute
value of z2 minus z1.

00:06:58.360 --> 00:06:59.720
Now, the t's cancel out here.

00:06:59.720 --> 00:07:00.980
We just got a one out front.

00:07:00.980 --> 00:07:06.210
So this is just equal to the
absolute value of z2 minus z1.

00:07:06.210 --> 00:07:08.890
So we see that
choice A does work.

00:07:08.890 --> 00:07:12.620
This plus this does
indeed equal that.

